  "texts": [
    "There is often a trade-off between a model's level of interpretability and fairness and the cost of achieving these goals [73].",
    "For example, adding interpretability or fairness constraints to a model may increase the computational cost of training or evaluating the model or require additional data collection or annotation, which refers to the burden.",
    "We must balance the burden of achieving a certain level of transparency or fairness against the potential benefits of using the model in a particular application.",
    "• Equality of effort: This concept is analyzed as a causalbased fairness approach, which refers to a notion of fairness in which individuals are judged based on their effort and not just their outcomes.",
    "According to the context of group fairness in machine learning, equality of effort requires that individuals who put in the same amount of effort (most other features have the same value) should have equal chances of success, regardless of any protected group status (such as race or gender) [80]."
  ],
